type mismatches in PagesPageConfig validation. | Failed at: ship | Suggestion: Add a `git fetch origin main` step before the ship stage's force-push to ensure the local ref is up-to-date with remote, and investigate whether the verify stage's retry logic is properly re-running type checks rather than passing cached results. | Flaw: ship — Git push rejected due to stale remote ref — no fetch/update before push | Stages: taskify:completed, plan:completed, build:completed, verify:completed, review:completed, review-fix:completed, ship:failed","createdAt":"2026-04-10T16:17:53.227Z","wordCount":963,"positions":[0,7,14,21,29,34,50,59,68,85,94,108,115,122,134,144,148,153,160,166,173,181,189,197,205,210,221,234,247,254,260,270,278,288,297,307,321,329,344,359,366,374,383,397,408,419,424,438,454,468,479,486,498,505,509,515,522,528,533,544,549,557,563,571,582,588,595,601,611,623,635,647,654,662,668,677,686,689,697,702,709,716,721,729,736,747,753,760,764,769,778,785,791,798,804,807,813,820,827,834,842,850,861,866,877,883,894,901,912,919,930,937,941,952,957]},"ep_stage_diary_001":{"taskId":"2288-260417-184341","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_001","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"build\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Plan files may fail to write to disk due to permission prompts; plan text is still submitted even if file write fails\",\"scope\":\"plan mode\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Priority labels use a `priority:` prefix (e.g., `priority:high`, `priority:medium`, `priority:low`)\",\"scope\":\"kody taskify\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When GH/MCP credentials are unavailable, `kody taskify` can run in local mode with `--file`, writing output to a JSON file\",\"scope\":\"kody taskify\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Taskify sub-issue bodies must contain ## Context, ## Acceptance Criteria, and ## Test Strategy sections\",\"scope\":\"kody taskify\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Kahn's algorithm is a reliable programmatic approach for verifying topological order of depends-on relationships\",\"scope\":\"verify-taskify.ts\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T19:08:07.812Z","wordCount":850,"positions":[2,10,18,31,38,47,54,59,69,77,86,91,98,109,118,123,131,137,147,155,160,166,174,182,187,196,203,216,223,232,239,246,257,272,281,289,298,308,317,325,333,338,350,357,366,378,381,385,401,415,420,433,440,446,459,466,474,486,491,498,506,511,523,530,543,550,558,562,568,575,580,591,603,614,631,636,645,656,664,669,681,688,699,706,713,728,737,750,763,773,785,794,805,821,829,836,844]},"ep_stage_diary_002":{"taskId":"2288-260417-184341","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_002","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"The verify.md overall result can show FAIL due to pre-existing errors in unrelated files outside the diff, even when the target task passes all checks.\",\"scope\":\"verify-taskify.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Unused variables (e.g. issueUrlPattern, issueNumbers) should be prefixed with _ or removed to avoid ESLint noise, even when they have no behavioral impact.\",\"scope\":\"verify-taskify.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Writing the plan file directly (without subagents or redundant exploration) avoids permission-prompt failures that plague plan-file write attempts.\",\"scope\":\"plan.md\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"kody taskify sub-issues use priority:high/medium/low labels and include ## Context, ## Acceptance Criteria, ## Test Strategy body sections.\",\"scope\":\"kody taskify\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-17T19:11:02.921Z","wordCount":838,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,59,66,69,77,88,93,98,105,109,118,128,138,144,156,162,176,183,188,199,209,217,224,232,239,246,255,262,269,285,302,326,345,356,362,369,376,396,399,410,420,428,435,443,450,457,468,475,487,492,497,507,515,528,538,551,558,569,576,590,597,602,607,613,625,633,638,645,652,665,672,677,685,689,696,700,709,714,721,725,736,747,759,770,783,788,797,802,814,822,827]},"ep_stage_diary_003":{"taskId":"2288-260417-184341","episodeId":"ep_stage_diary_003","source":"stage_diary","content":"{\"stage\":\"review-fix\",\"insights\":[{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"When a plan file can't be written to disk (permission prompts), submit the plan as text instead — it still executes normally.\",\"scope\":\"pipeline/plan.md\"},{\"kind\":\"gotcha\",\"text\":\"Unused variables (e.g., `issueUrlPattern`, `issueNumbers`) declared but not read will cause ESLint failures in verify scripts — prefix with `_` to suppress.\",\"scope\":\"verify-taskify.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Use Kahn's algorithm for topological ordering verification — clean, O(V+E), and unambiguous compared to manual comparisons.\",\"scope\":\"topo order verification\"},{\"kind\":\"decision\",\"text\":\"Run `kody taskify` in local mode (no MCP/GH credentials required) and read from `taskify-result.json` for deterministic scripted verification.\",\"scope\":\"kody taskify verification\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Verify script failures in `verify.md` can be driven by pre-existing errors in unrelated files — isolate verification to only the target output.\",\"scope\":\"","createdAt":"2026-04-17T19:12:38.557Z","wordCount":1000,"positions":[2,10,17,23,36,43,52,66,71,85,96,102,113,123,134,142,147,160,166,175,187,195,204,209,216,223,232,239,246,264,283,298,311,315,325,331,338,350,357,367,386,398,406,413,421,428,435,446,453,457,464,478,490,499,514,533,545,557,564,579,587,592,598,615,622,633,640,645,650,662,668,674,677,681,684,696,710,721,729,736,746,760,769,785,793,798,806,823,830,839,846,853,860,873,880,891,901,905,914,924,934,942,950,966,975,982,992]}},"totalDocs":4}